# Code Review Checklist

Run **`make audit`** before every commit. It must pass. If `go` is missing from PATH in an agent shell, fix the environment or Makefile discovery (see `git-workflow` / Makefile)—do not treat “audit skipped” as shippable.

## Code Quality

- [ ] `make audit` passes (test + lint + vet + vulncheck + tidy)
- [ ] No new `//nolint` without explanation: `//nolint:errcheck // reason`
- [ ] Error messages: lowercase, no trailing punctuation
- [ ] Errors wrapped with context at every boundary
- [ ] `context.Context` propagated to all I/O operations
- [ ] No shared mutable state without `sync.Mutex` or channels
- [ ] SQL uses parameterized queries only
- [ ] Slices pre-allocated when size is known: `make([]T, 0, n)`
- [ ] No new dependencies without justification

## Testing

- [ ] New/changed code has corresponding `_test.go` changes
- [ ] Tests use `t.Parallel()` and table-driven pattern
- [ ] `go test -race` passes

## YAITracker

- [ ] **`begin_work`** at start and **`complete_work`** at end for the issue — **blocking** when YAIT MCP is enabled (see `.cursor/rules/yaitracker-workflow.mdc`)
- [ ] Completion summary describes what changed, files touched, tests added

## Git

- [ ] Commit follows conventional commits format
- [ ] Commit body includes **`Refs: YAIT-N`** or **`Refs: none`** (hook-enforced)
- [ ] Branch matches **`feature/YAIT-N-…`** or **`fix/YAIT-N-…`** (or release/hotfix per `git-workflow.mdc`)
- [ ] Landed via **PR** to `develop` (or release/hotfix flow)—not direct push of work commits to `origin/develop` / `origin/master`
- [ ] One logical change per commit
